## Framework consultation — read-only

The `consultation/` folder holds **framework meta-docs**, not product documentation. It describes how to document products; do not treat it as the product tree.



## Do not edit consultation files

**Do not create, modify, or delete files under `consultation/`** unless the user **explicitly** asks to change that folder (e.g. “update `consultation/structure.md`”, “edit templates.md in consultation”).

When unsure whether a request targets consultation vs product docs, ask before editing.


## Read 
[structure.md](../consultation/structure.md)



## Before updating any product file

Read [templates.md](../consultation/templates.md) for the target file shape and this file for layout. Match the template shape, required sections, and ID conventions before writing.



## When writing some text to the chat
Be precise. Don't put long texts - 1 screen max.
